	<h3 class="title"><a href="/279191#comment-3010811" class="active">Lest we forget Cocaine, Alcohol &amp; other secret ingredients.</a></h3>
    <div class="submitted active">Submitted by <a href="/user/29229" title="View user profile.">Mark Twain</a> on Fri, 03/22/2013 - 16:42.  <a class="permalink" href="/comment/3010811">Permalink</a></div>
	<div class="content">
     <p><img src="http://img576.imageshack.us/img576/540/allsizesthenotebookfoun.jpg" /> <a href="http://www.teachat.com/viewtopic.php?f=11&amp;t=15128" title="http://www.teachat.com/viewtopic.php?f=11&amp;t=15128" rel="nofollow">http://www.teachat.com/viewtopic.php?f=11&amp;t=15128</a> Coca Cola recipe 'discovered?' After discovery, is it still a secret recipe? Original? When did coca disappear?</p>
<p>The official recipe is said to be guarded 24-hours a day in a vault in Atlanta, Georgia. The 'secret recipe:'<br />
Fluid extract of Coca 3 drams USP</p>
<ul>Citric acid 3 oz<br />
Caffeine 1oz<br />
Sugar 30 (marking unclear on quantity)<br />
Water 2.5 gal<br />
Lime juice 2 pints 1 qrt<br />
Vanilla 1oz<br />
Caramel 1.5oz or more to colour<br />
7X flavour (use 2oz of flavour to 5 gals syrup):
<ul><b>Alcohol 8oz</b><br />
Orange oil 20 drops<br />
Lemon oil 30 drops<br />
Nutmeg oil 10 drops<br />
Coriander 5 drops<br />
Neroli 10 drops<br />
Cinnamon 10 drops</ul>
</ul>
